23_AM.jpg"/></noscript></span></div></div></div></div></div><div class="duet--media--caption pt-6 font-polysans-mono text-12 font-light leading-130 tracking-1"><figcaption class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup inline text-gray-13 dark:text-gray-e9 [&amp;&gt;a:hover]:text-black [&amp;&gt;a:hover]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;&gt;a:hover]:text-gray-e9 dark:[&amp;&gt;a:hover]:shadow-underline-gray-63 [&amp;&gt;a]:shadow-underline-gray-13 dark:[&amp;&gt;a]:shadow-underline-gray-63"><em>Using the </em><a href="https://apps.apple.com/de/app/discovery-dns-sd-browser/id305441017"><em>Discovery</em></a> app, <em>I can see all the Thread border routers on my network, including devices from, Nanoleaf, Google, Samsung, Apple, and Amazon.</em></figcaption></div></div><div class="mb-20 w-full sm:mb-0 sm:w-1/2"><div class="transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out"><div class="fixed inset-0 h-[110vh] w-full bg-white transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out z-[-1] cursor-default opacity-0" role="button" aria-label="Close" tabindex="0"></div><div role="button" aria-label="Zoom" tabindex="0" class="visible z-30 w-full origin-center transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out cursor-zoom-in"><div class="relative transition duration-75 ease-in-out p-0"><div class=""><div class=""><span style="box-sizing:border-box;display:block;overflow:hidden;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;position:relative"><span style="box-sizing:border-box;display:block;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;padding-top:216.4102564102564%"></span><img alt="The Nanoleaf app shows my five individual Thread networks. Nanoleaf’s border router has joined the Apple network, but the others are on their own." src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" decoding="async" data-nimg="responsive" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover"/><noscript><img alt="The Nanoleaf app shows my five individual Thread networks. Nanoleaf’s border router has joined the Apple network, but the others are on their own." loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-nimg="responsive" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 100vw, (max-width: 1023px) 50vw, 350px" srcSet="https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1170x2532/256x554/filters:focal(585x1266:586x1267):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24830067/IMG_F1C26339DCEF_1.jpeg 256w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1170x2532/376x814/filters:focal(585x1266:586x1267):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24830067/IMG_F1C26339DCEF_1.jpeg 376w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1170x2532/384x831/filters:focal(585x1266:586x1267):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24830067/IMG_F1C26339DCEF_1.jpeg 384w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1170x2532/415x898/filters:focal(585x1266:586x1267):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24830067/IMG_F1C26339DCEF_1.jpeg 415w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1170x2532/480x1039/filters:focal(585x1266:586x1267):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24830067/IMG_F1C26339DCEF_1.jpeg 480w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1170x2532/540x1168/filters:focal(585x1266:586x1267):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24830067/IMG_F1C26339DCEF_1.jpeg 540w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1170x2532/640x1385/filters:focal(585x1266:586x1267):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24830067/IMG_F1C26339DCEF_1.jpeg 640w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1