dwidth needs such as cameras. If Matter had provided a secure, simple, local way to unify those protocols, it might be in a better place today."},"dropcap":true,"endmark":false,"lead":true},{"__typename":"EntryBodyParagraph","placement":{"id":"q1c6hC","alignment":null},"__isEntryBodyComponent":"EntryBodyParagraph","contents":{"html":"Instead, Matter chose to use Wi-Fi and Thread for wireless communication, with other protocols needing to “bridge” into Matter, requiring an extra step from manufacturers that \u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/3/27/23658961/philips-hue-matter-bridge-update-delayed\"\u003efew have chosen to implement.\u003c/a\u003e So, why pick the relatively new Thread over existing options? "},"dropcap":false,"endmark":false,"lead":false},{"__typename":"EntryBodyParagraph","placement":{"id":"MBrRTd","alignment":null},"__isEntryBodyComponent":"EntryBodyParagraph","contents":{"html":"Probably politics. Two of the largest players in bringing Matter to fruition — Apple and Google — were already fully onboard the Thread smart home train when the \u003ca href=\"https://csa-iot.org/all-solutions/matter/\"\u003eConnectivity Standards Alliance\u003c/a\u003e (CSA), the group behind Matter, was formed. (\u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/22787729/matter-smart-home-standard-apple-amazon-google#:~:text=What%20is%20Thread%2C%20and%20why%20is%20it%20better%3F\"\u003eThread was originally developed by Nest\u003c/a\u003e, pre-Google, back in the early 2010s.) Plus, Thread is based on Zigbee, and the CSA was formerly the Zigbee Alliance. "},"dropcap":false,"endmark":false,"lead":false},{"__typename":"EntryBodyParagraph","placement":{"id":"rVZzlF","alignment":null},"__isEntryBodyComponent":"EntryBodyParagraph","contents":{"html":"But while the \u003ca href=\"https://www.threadgroup.org/Portals/0/documents/support/Thread%20Network%20Fundamentals_v3.pdf\"\u003eopen-sourced Thread protocol\u003c/a\u003e does have compelling features (see sidebar), its rollout as part of the major shift Matter is trying to make in our smart homes needed to be better."},"dropcap":false,"endmark":false,"lead":false},{"__typename":"EntryBodyRelatedList","placement":{"id":"eFZywc","alignment":"WIDE_BLOCK"},"__isEntryBodyComponent":"EntryBodyRelatedList","items":[{"title":"Thread is Matter’s secret sauce for a better\u0026nbsp;smart home","url":"https://www.theverge.com/23165855/thread-smart-home-protocol-matter-apple-google-interview"},{"title":"Matter’s plan to save the smart home ","url":"https://www.theverge.com/22787729/matter-smart-home-standard-apple-amazon-google"},{"title":"What Thread 1.3.0 means for Matter","url":"https://www.theverge.com/2022/7/19/23269460/thread-1-3-0-matter-border-routers-homepod-mini-echo-nest"}]},{"__typename":"EntryBodyParagraph","placement":{"id":"ubRh31","alignment":null},"__isEntryBodyComponent":"EntryBodyParagraph","contents":{"html":"The problem is the current state of the Thread infrastructure: in particular, \u003ca href=\"https://openthread.io/guides/border-router#:~:text=A%20Thread%20Border%20Router%20connects,to%20connect%20to%20other%20networks.\"\u003eThread border routers\u003c/a\u003e, which Thread devices need to connect to the internet and other IP-based networks. There are still relatively \u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23568091/matter-compatible-devices-accessories-apple-amazon-google-samsung\"\u003efew Thread devices\u003c/a\u003e available to buy, and some platforms only halfheartedly support the protocol (\u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/5/2/23707900/amazon-matter-smart-home-thread-support\"\u003emost notably Amazon\u003c/a\u003e), making buying and setting up Thread-powered gadgets confusing and complicated. "},"dropcap":false,"endmark":false,"lead":false},{"__typename":"EntryBodyParagraph","placement":{"id":"ArItYC","alignment":null},"__isEntryBodyComponent":"EntryBodyParagraph","contents":{"html":"But the overarching issue is the inability of the major platforms t